SDLC Phases & Trending Technologies (2025)
1. Requirement Analysis & Planning

Who works here: Product Manager, Business Analyst, UX Researcher, Solution Architect.

What happens: Understanding business needs, defining requirements, feasibility study, risk analysis.

Trending Tools/Tech:

Product Management: Jira, ClickUp, Notion, Confluence, Linear.

Requirement Gathering: Miro, Figma (for brainstorming + UX research).

Communication: Slack, MS Teams, Loom, FigJam.

AI Assistants: ChatGPT, Notion AI, Linear Insights for requirement drafting.

2. System Design (Architecture & UI/UX)

Who works here: Solution Architects, UI/UX Designers, Tech Leads.

What happens: High-level & low-level design (architecture, database, API contracts, UI/UX flow).

Trending Tools/Tech:

UI/UX Design: Figma, Adobe XD, Framer.

Architecture: Lucidchart, Draw.io, Whimsical, PlantUML.

Cloud-native Design: AWS Well-Architected Tool, GCP Architecture Center, Azure Design Studio.

Microservices & Event-driven Patterns: Kafka, gRPC, GraphQL.

3. Development (Coding & Implementation)

Who works here: Developers (Frontend, Backend, Fullstack, Mobile, AI/ML Engineers).

What happens: Building features according to requirements.

Trending Tech Stacks:

Frontend: React, Next.js, Vue 3, SvelteKit, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui.

Backend: Node.js (Express, NestJS), Spring Boot (Java), Django/FastAPI (Python), GoLang.

Databases: PostgreSQL, MongoDB, MySQL, Redis, Cassandra, Firebase.

APIs: GraphQL, REST, tRPC.

Mobile: React Native, Flutter, Swift (iOS), Kotlin (Android).

AI/ML Development: PyTorch, TensorFlow, HuggingFace, LangChain, OpenAI API.

Version Control: Git, GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket.

4. Testing (QA & Automation)

Who works here: QA Engineers, Automation Engineers, SDET (Software Development Engineer in Test).

What happens: Validate features, catch bugs, automate tests.

Trending Tools/Tech:

Automation: Selenium, Cypress, Playwright.

API Testing: Postman, Newman, Karate.

Mobile Testing: Appium, Detox.

Unit Testing: Jest, Mocha, PyTest, JUnit.

CI/CD Testing: GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Jenkins.

AI-powered Testing: Testim.io, Mabl, BrowserStack with AI.

5. Deployment (Release & Delivery)

Who works here: DevOps Engineers, Release Engineers, Cloud Engineers.

What happens: Deploy applications to servers/cloud, monitor reliability.

Trending Tools/Tech:

CI/CD: GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, CircleCI, ArgoCD.

Containers & Orchestration: Docker, Kubernetes, Helm.

Cloud Platforms: AWS, Azure, GCP, DigitalOcean, Vercel, Netlify.

Serverless: AWS Lambda, Cloudflare Workers, Firebase Functions.

6. Operations & Monitoring

Who works here: DevOps, Site Reliability Engineers (SRE), CloudOps.

What happens: Monitoring performance, uptime, logs, scaling systems.

Trending Tools/Tech:

Monitoring: Prometheus, Grafana, Datadog, New Relic.

Logging: ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana), Loki.

Error Tracking: Sentry, Rollbar.

Infrastructure as Code: Terraform, Pulumi, Ansible.

7. Maintenance & Support

Who works here: Tech Support, Customer Success, Engineers on call.

What happens: Bug fixes, updates, security patches, customer queries.

Trending Tools/Tech:

Ticketing: Zendesk, Freshdesk, Jira Service Desk.

Customer Feedback: Intercom, Crisp, Hotjar.

Automation: AI Chatbots (Drift, ChatGPT-based bots).

Observability: OpenTelemetry, Honeycomb.

ðŸš€ Bonus Layer (Across All Phases)

Collaboration: GitHub Copilot, ChatGPT, Cursor AI.

Security (DevSecOps): Snyk, OWASP ZAP, Checkmarx, Prisma Cloud.

Agile/DevOps Practices: Scrum, Kanban, CI/CD, Infrastructure as Code.

AI Integration: AI coding assistants, AI testing tools, AI monitoring bots.
